openstack_governance/projects_schema.yam.message:
I agree with Jay that a version identifier is a string, not a number.  The periods are separators, not decimal points, so these aren't "really" numbers.  Since the TC has specified elsewhere that the only valid release names will be of the form

  <year>.{1,2}

I guess we can get away with calling these numbers, but in general, I don't think it's a good idea.

